I took OS/X and Java 1.4.2 out of the picture, by starting up a crawl on a RedHat Linux 
machine with Java 1.5.  I noticed Java 1.5 provides toe thread stack dumps.

Seems like a lot of time is being spent in "expungeStaleEntries" -- is this normal behavior 
as the crawl gets bigger?
